title.narrative: 5.2 CP SYSTEMS

description.narrative: Government welfare and justice institutions in Somaliland, Somalia and Puntland adopt legislative and policy frameworks to protect boys and girls from all forms of abuse, neglect and exploitation., which contributes to Access To Justice, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, increased numbers of children in Somalia are protected from all forms of abuse, neglect and exploitation

title.narrative: Government welfare and justice institutions in Somaliland, Somalia and Puntland adopt legislative and policy frameworks to protectboys and girls from all forms of abuse, neglect and exploitation.

description.narrative: Good progress was registered in the development and operationalization of child protection related legislative and policy initiatives as well as in relation to the justice for children sector (mainly in Puntland), birth registration programming (in both Somaliland and Puntland), and social welfare sector capacity strengthening and deployment during COVID-19.; As part of the child protection systems strengthening program, UNICEF continued to support government line ministries to enhance the capacity and professionalism of the social service workforce as well as strengthen child protection service provision (preventive and response). | Status:Met | As-of Date:10/01/2021
